This paper deals with a fundamental problem in query processing, which is a common topic in database research (cs.DB). The problem involves finding pairs of strings based on their edit distance, which is also relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed algorithm is based on string partitions and hash values, which are common techniques in data structures (cs.DS) and data mining (cs.DM).
